fallback_letters:
Dear {name},

The spring flowers are out at last and they made me think of you straight away! The daffodils along our old road are simply beautiful this year. I was smiling to myself remembering that lovely summer we spent at the seaside — do you remember how we laughed? What sunshine those days were! I wonder, what is your favourite memory of a summer's day?

With love, {friend}

Dear {name},

I hope this finds you well and in good spirits! The autumn leaves are turning the most gorgeous shades of gold and copper — it feels like the whole world is putting on a show just for us. I was thinking about those wonderful Saturday dances we used to go to. What a time that was! Do you have a favourite song from those happy days?

With love, {friend}

Dear {name},

Winter has arrived and brought such a cosy feeling with it! I have been thinking of you over a warm cup of tea. Do you remember the old tea shop on the High Street? Such lovely cream scones they made there. It always feels like those simple, happy moments were the best of all. What is the meal or treat that always makes you smile?

With love, {friend}

Dear {name},

Summer is here and the garden is looking so lovely! Everything in bloom reminds me of you. I was walking past the old dance hall yesterday and found myself humming one of our favourite tunes. Isn't it funny how music can take you right back? Tell me — what was the song that always got you up on your feet?

With love, {friend}
